'''Isḥaqq Nyutun''', amɣar n tdrawt tagldant (gr 1642 d 1726), iga [[Tusnakt|usnak]], [[Tasngama|asngam]], astronomer, theologian d umara [[Tutlayt Tanglizt|anglizi]]. Ittussan ɣ umaḍal mas iga ɣ inmɣurn n isunakn d isngamn d ig yan ɣ imassan mqqurnin ɣ [[Amzruy|umzruy]] n [[Afgan|ufgan]].

Adllis nns (''Mathematical Principles of Natural Philosophy''), lli itturan s [[Tutlayt Talatint|tlatinit]], iffuɣ-d ɣ usggʷas n 1687, iga ɣ yan n idllisn lli snflnin iẓṛi n ufgan f [[Amaḍal|umaḍal]], s lahwan tt akkʷ lliɣ rad gis issfal [[tamikanikt]] taklasikit.

'''Nyuten''' iskr tugt n tuwuri ɣ mad iẓlin s ''optics'' d yiws ɣ usbuɣlu n usmiḍn/lḥsab n ''calculus''.

Ɣ ''Principia'', '''Nyuten''' ismd ilgamn n umussu d ''universal gravitation'' lli akkʷ igan ttmi n iẓṛi n imassan aylliɣ tt tzri ''theory of relativity'' lli isker ''Einstein''.

